[1] India, poultry
AVIAN INFLUENZA IN INDIA
Follow-up report No. 1
See also: <http://www.oie.int/eng/info/hebdo/AIS_30.HTM#Sec6> 23 Feb 2006

Information received on 23 Feb 2006 from Mr P.M.A. Hakeem, Secretary to the
Government of India, Ministry of Agriculture, Department of Animal Husbandry
and Dairying, New Delhi:
End of the previous report period: 18 Feb 2006 (see Disease Information, 19
[8], 133, dated 23 Feb 2006).
End of this report period: 23 Feb 2006.
Identification of agent: highly pathogenic avian influenza virus subtype H5N1.
Date of first confirmation of the event: 18 Feb 2006.
Date of start of the event: 27 Jan 2006.
Clinical disease: yes.
Nature of diagnosis: post-mortem and laboratory.
Details of outbreak (reminder):
First administrative division (State)/Lower administrative division
(district)/Type of epidemiological unit
Maharashtra/ Nandurbar/ village
Name of the location/Date of start of the outbreak/Species
Navapur/ 27 Jan 2006/ avi
Number of animals in the outbreaks:
susceptible / cases / deaths / destroyed / slaughtered
[unknown]
Description of affected population: poultry
Source of outbreaks or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.
Control measures undertaken:
- movement control inside the country;
- stamping out;
- disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s).
Due to the very small number of poultry in the infected and surveillance
zones, we have resorted to stamping out in the entire 10-km radius infected
zone. To date, no further cases of avian influenza have been reported from
this area or from any other parts of the country.
Treatment of affected animals: no.
Final report: no.
******
[2] Malaysia, poultry
AVIAN INFLUENZA IN MALAYSIA
(Date of previous outbreak of avian influenza in Malaysia reported to the OIE:
3 Jan 2005).
Immediate notification report
Information received on 23 Feb 2006 from Dr Hawari Bin Hussein, Director
General, Department of Veterinary Service, Ministry of Agriculture, Kuala
Lumpur:
Report date: 23 Feb 2006.
Reason for immediate notification: re-occurrence of a listed disease or
infection in a country, zone/compartment following a report declaring the
outbreak(s) ended.
Identification of agent: highly pathogenic avian influenza H5N1.
Date of first confirmation of the event: 19 Feb 2006.
Date of start of the event: 6 Feb 2006.
Clinical disease: yes.
Nature of diagnosis: laboratory.
Details of outbreak:
First administrative division (state)/ Lower administrative division (city)/
Type of epidemiological unit/
Wilayah Persekutuan/ Setapak/ village
Name of the location (village)/ Latitude/ Longitude/ Date of start of the
outbreak / Species
Pasir Wardieburn/ 3 deg 11.563 N / 101 deg 43.023 E/ 6 Feb.2006/ avi
Number of animals in the outbreak:
susceptible/ cases/ deaths/ destroyed/ slaughtered
150/ 50/ 50/ 100/ 0
Description of affected population: free-range village chickens.
Diagnosis:
Laboratories where diagnostic tests were performed/ Species examined
Regional Veterinary Laboratory, Petaling Jaya/ avi
Diagnostic tests used/ Date/ Result
virus isolation;- RT-PCR/ 18 Feb. 2006/ Positive for H5
Laboratories where diagnostic tests were performed/ Species examined
Veterinary Research Institute/ avi
Diagnostic tests used/ Date/ Result
- RT-PCR (M gene);- RT-PCR (H5 gene);- RT-PCR (N1 gene)/ 19 Feb. 2006/
Positive for H5N1
Source of outbreak or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive.
Control measures undertaken:
- stamping out;
- quarantine;
- movement control inside the country;
- screening;
- zoning;
- disinfection of infected premises/establishment(s);
- dipping/spraying.
Treatment of affected animals: no.
Vaccination prohibited: yes.
Other details/comments:
A 1km-radius Infected Zone was established around the index case. Culling in
the infected Zone started on 20 Feb 2006 and was completed on 22 Feb 2006
(1970 chickens, 62 ducks and 72 other birds). In addition, 505 eggs were also
destroyed.
A 10-km-radius Surveillance Zone was also established. Clinical and laboratory
surveillance is underway in the Surveillance Zone. Surveillance is also
underway in other States.
Final report: no.
******
